The paper deals with secure communication in multi-cell multi-user massive MIMO systems, which involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), cryptography (cs.CR), signal processing (cs.MM), and security and privacy (cs.SI). The paper specifically focuses on the design of a data-aided secure downlink transmission scheme to combat active eavesdropping, which is a problem that falls under the purview of all these sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT, followed by cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.MM, and cs.SI.
